title: MSN exploit
description:
Want revenge on someone in you\&#039;re messangers contact list? Well, you\&#039;re search ends here! this program uses an exploit (found by myself) in MSN messanger that when targeted at the users email address will cause you\&#039;re victims MSN Clients to have a buffer overflow the result is his client crashing. Basically that\&#039;s all to be said about this proggy.

As a side note, No it is not a trojan or Virus So don\&#039;t post that it is! However it is malware and Anti-Virus programs will ofcourse detect malware (google - define:malware) malware doesnt mean it\&#039;s a virus, trojan or worm.. it basically means it\&#039;s used for evil deeds ;) and ofcourse, kicking a person from msn is an evil deed.

Have fun and get it while this exploit is not fixed by Microsoft!
